E-Commerce Power BI Dashboard

This Power BI project focuses on analyzing e-commerce business performance by transforming raw sales data into meaningful visual insights. The dashboard provides a comprehensive view of sales, profit, and customer behavior across different product categories, regions, and time periods.

üîç Key Insights Displayed

Sales Overview: Total revenue, profit, and quantity sold across various periods (monthly, quarterly, or yearly).
Category & Subcategory Performance: Identify which product categories contribute most to total sales and profit.
Regional Analysis: Compare sales and profitability across different regions, countries, or states to identify top-performing areas.
Customer Analysis: Track repeat customers, average order value, and purchase trends to understand customer behavior.
Top Products: Visualize best-selling and least-performing products to guide inventory and marketing decisions.

‚öôÔ∏è Power BI Features Used

Interactive filters & slicers for dynamic exploration by date, region, and category.
DAX formulas to calculate KPIs such as profit margin, YoY growth, and average sales.
Data cleaning & modeling using Power Query for accurate relationships and measures.
Visual storytelling through KPI cards, line charts, bar charts, maps, and trend visuals.

üéØ Objective

To enable data-driven decisions for an e-commerce business by providing clear, interactive insights into sales trends, profitability, and customer behavior.

üí° Impact

This dashboard helps stakeholders:
Identify profitable products and regions
Understand customer purchase trends
Monitor performance metrics in real time
Make informed marketing and inventory decisions
